==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Revivification
<hw>Re*viv`i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧vivification</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Renewal of
life; restoration of life; the act of recalling, or the state of being
recalled, to life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld> <def>The reduction of a metal from
a state of combination to its metallic state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revivify</ent>⟦br⟧
